SettingsType.name: HDR Exposure
SettingsType.info: HDR exposure of atmosphere: More lets in a lot of sun

SettingsType.name: Lacunarity
SettingsType.info: Lacunarity defines the overall shape of the fractal, high lacunarity = lots of "lakes"

SettingsType.name: Atmosphere color
SettingsType.info: Variations: normal, bleak, red, cyan, green, purple, yellow, pink. Can be separated by comma, will choose one by random.

SettingsType.name: Hill threshold
SettingsType.info: Hill normal threshold. 1 = Everything has hill texture (0 degrees from normal), 1 = nothing (90 degrees)

SettingsType.name: Top threshold
SettingsType.info: Top threshold. Above this value (multiplied with the radius), all colors are top color.

SettingsType.name: Basin threshold
SettingsType.info: Basin threshold. Below this value (multiplied with the radius), all colors are basin colors.

SettingsType.name: Sea level
SettingsType.info: Sea level. Below this value (multiplied with the radius), Everything is sea.

SettingsType.name: Cloud scattering
SettingsType.info: Cloud noise amplitude falloff frequency. Large value = small scale perturbations, low value = large scale.

SettingsType.name: Cloud subtract value
SettingsType.info: Value to subtract from cloud, higher value yields scattered clouds.

SettingsType.name: Cloud thickness
SettingsType.info: Alpha value of clouds. Set to 0 to remove clouds completely.
